HashMap
A HashMap in Java is a data structure that stores data in key → value pairs.
HashMap<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();

HashMap works on hashing.
You give a key
Java converts it into a number using hashCode()
That number decides where the data is stored


Internal Structure
At its core:
Array of buckets → Each bucket stores nodes (entries)

Key Features
Stores key-value pairs
Keys must be unique
Values can be duplicated
Allows one null key
Allows multiple null values
Not synchronized (not thread-safe)
No guaranteed order

| Operation | Average | Worst Case |
| --------- | ------- | ---------- |
| Put       | O(1)    | O(log n)   |
| Get       | O(1)    | O(log n)   |
| Remove    | O(1)    | O(log n)   |


